  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Punto 5\n",
    "\n",
    "5. Demostrar que\n",
    "$$\n",
    "diag(A \\cdot B) = \\sum_{cols} A \\odot B^T = np.sum(A \\odot B^T, axis=1)\n",
    "$$ es decir, que se puede \"esquivar\" la matriz de $n \\times n$ usando matrices de $n \\times p$. También se puede usar, de forma equivalente,\n",
    "$$\n",
    "np.sum(A^T \\odot B, axis=0).T\n",
    "$$\n",
    "queda a preferencia del alumno cuál usar.\n",
    "\n",
    "Sean $\\mathrm{A} \\in \\mathbb{R}^{n \\times p}$ y $\\mathrm{B}  \\in \\mathbb{R}^{p \\times n}$. Sabemos que $\\mathrm{A}\\mathrm{B}  \\in \\mathbb{R}^{n \\times n}$ es una matriz cuadrada. \n",
    "\n",
    "Se quiere mostrar que los elementos de la diagonal de $\\mathrm{A}\\mathrm{B}$ se pueden obtener como suma sobre las columnas de la matriz  $\\mathrm{A} \\odot \\mathrm{B}^{\\mathrm{T}}$, donde $\\odot$ representa el producto de Hadamard:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "(\\mathcal{A} \\odot \\mathcal{B})_{ij}=(\\mathcal{A})_{ij}(\\mathcal{B})_{ij}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Primero, hay que notar que, por definicion de producto de matrices, los elementos de la matriz $\\mathrm{A}\\mathrm{B}$ son simplemente productos internos canonicos entre los vectores que forman las filas de $\\mathrm{A}$ y las columnas de $\\mathrm{B}$:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\left( \\mathrm{A} \\mathrm{B} \\right)_{i,j}= \\displaystyle \\sum_{k=1}^p (\\mathrm{A})_{ik}(\\mathrm{B})_{kj} \\quad \\forall i\\in[1,n] \\text{ y } \\forall j\\in[1,n]\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Ahora, como solo interesan los elementos en la diagonal de $\\mathrm{A} \\mathrm{B}$, interesan los casos en los que $i=j=l$: \n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\left( \\mathrm{A} \\mathrm{B} \\right)_{l,l}= \\displaystyle \\sum_{k=1}^p (\\mathrm{A})_{lk}(\\mathrm{B})_{kl} \\quad \\forall l\\in[1,n]\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Por otro lado, el producto de Hadamard entre $\\mathrm{A}$ y $\\mathrm{B}^{\\mathrm{T}}$ es\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\left(\\mathrm{A} \\odot \\mathrm{B}^{\\mathrm{T}} \\right)_{ij}=(\\mathrm{A})_{ij}\\left(\\mathrm{B}^{\\mathrm{T}}\\right)_{ij} = (\\mathrm{A})_{ij}(\\mathrm{B})_{ji} \\quad  \\forall i \\in [1,n] \\text{ y } \\forall j \\in [1,p]\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Pero si se suman los elementos de la $l$-esima columna de esta matriz se obtiene\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\sum_{j=1}^{p} \\left(\\mathrm{A} \\odot \\mathrm{B}^{\\mathrm{T}} \\right)_{lj} = \\sum_{j=1}^{p} (\\mathrm{A})_{lj}(\\mathrm{B})_{jl} \\quad \\forall l \\in [1,n]\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Combinando todo, se tiene\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\left( \\mathrm{A} \\mathrm{B} \\right)_{l,l}= \\displaystyle \\sum_{k=1}^p (\\mathrm{A})_{lk}(\\mathrm{B})_{kl} = \\sum_{j=1}^{p} \\left(\\mathrm{A} \\odot \\mathrm{B}^{\\mathrm{T}} \\right)_{lj} \\quad \\forall l \\in [1,n]\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "que es lo que se queria mostrar."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Punto 6\n",
    "\n",
    "6. Utilizar la propiedad antes demostrada para reimplementar la predicción del modelo `FasterQDA` de forma eficiente en un nuevo modelo `EfficientQDA`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class EfficientQDA(TensorizedQDA):\n",
    "    \"\"\"QDA implementation that predicts all observations at once.\n",
    "       Uses the property proved in the previous cell for a more efficient\n",
    "       calculation of the quadratic form.\"\"\"\n",
    "    def __init__(self):\n",
    "        super(EfficientQDA, self).__init__()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def predict(self, X):\n",
    "        \"\"\"For a (𝑝, 𝑛) array, return a (1, 𝑛) array with a prediction for each observation.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Check for appropriate shape in case of single prediction.\n",
    "        X = np.expand_dims(X, axis=1) if len(X.shape) == 1 else X\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # First, we need the unbiased X tensor.\n",
    "        ub_X = X - self.tensor_means                                          # Shape (𝑘, 𝑝, 𝑛)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Get quadratic form, using the property form the previous cell.\n",
    "        icov_ev = np.sum(\n",
    "            ub_X.transpose(0,2,1) * (self.tensor_inv_cov @ ub_X).transpose(0,2,1), \n",
    "            axis=2)                                                           # Shape (𝑘, 𝑛)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Now, I need the log of the determinants.\n",
    "        log_dets = np.log(LA.det(self.tensor_inv_cov))                        # Shape (𝑘,)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Now, we just need to calculate the log conditional.\n",
    "        log_conditional = 0.5*np.expand_dims(log_dets, axis=1) - 0.5*icov_ev  # Shape (𝑘, 1) - shape (𝑘, 𝑛) = shape (𝑘, 𝑛)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Get the sum of the (logarithmic) prior and conditional\n",
    "        logsum = np.expand_dims(self.log_a_priori, axis=1) + log_conditional  # Shape (𝑘, 1) + shape (𝑘, 𝑛) = shape (𝑘, 𝑛)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Now we need the class that maximizes the logsum (for each observation)\n",
    "        return np.argmax(logsum, axis=0, keepdims=True)                       # Shape (1, 𝑛), as desired."
   ]
