   "source": [
    "Como se esperaba, la descomposicion de Cholesky por si sola ofrece algunas mejoras. Aunque no compite con las implementaciones tensoriales de QDA, si lo hace con `QDA`. Se observa que las implementaciones `QDA_Chol1` y `QDA_Chol3` son similares a `QDA` en entrenamiento, y en memoria, pero mas rapidas en testeo. La implementacion `QDA_Chol2` es similar en entrenamiento y en memoria, pero significativamente mas lenta que `QDA` en testeo.\n",
    "\n",
    "Como `QDA_Chol1` y `QDA_Chol3` son similares, y mejores en testeo que `QDA_Chol2`, no creo que se pueda argumentar que alguna de estas dos sea claramente mejor. A pesar de esto, creo que se puede afirmar que `QDA_Chol2` parece ser peor que las otras dos, simplemente por la diferencia de performance en testeo.\n",
    "\n",
    "Para lo que sigue, se va a utilizar la implementacion `QDA_Chol3`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Punto 12\n",
    "\n",
    "12. Implementar el modelo `TensorizedChol` paralelizando sobre clases/observaciones según corresponda. Se recomienda heredarlo de alguna de las implementaciones de `QDA_Chol`, aunque la elección de cuál de ellas queda a cargo del alumno según lo observado en los benchmarks de puntos anteriores."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 29,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class TensorizedChol(QDA_Chol3):\n",
    "    \"\"\"QDA implementation that uses Cholesky decomposition for the covariance\n",
    "    matrices and parallelizes over the classes.\"\"\"\n",
    "    def __init__(self):\n",
    "        super(TensorizedChol, self).__init__()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def _fit_params(self, X, y):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Fit parameters and stack.\"\"\"\n",
    "        super()._fit_params(X,y)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Stack.\n",
    "        self.tensor_L_invs = np.stack(self.L_invs)                                     # Shape (𝑘,𝑝,𝑝)\n",
    "        self.tensor_means = np.stack(self.means)                                       # Shape (𝑘,𝑝,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "    def _predict_log_conditionals(self,x):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Predict logarithm of conditionals for all clases.\"\"\"\n",
    "        # Get unbiased x and calculate it's product with L inverse.\n",
    "        unbiased_x = x - self.tensor_means                                             # Shape (𝑘,𝑝,1)\n",
    "        y = self.tensor_L_invs @ unbiased_x                                            # Shape (𝑘,𝑝,𝑝) * (𝑘,𝑝,1) = (𝑘,𝑝,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Determinant calculation.\n",
    "        det_arr = np.log(\n",
    "            np.diagonal(\n",
    "                self.tensor_L_invs, offset=0, axis1=1, axis2=2\n",
    "            ).prod(axis=1)\n",
    "        )                                                                              # Shape (𝑘,𝑝,𝑝) -diag-> (𝑘,𝑝) -prod-> (𝑘,)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return det_arr - 0.5 * (y**2).squeeze().sum(axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "    def _predict_one(self, x):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Predict one observation.\"\"\"\n",
    "        return np.argmax(self.log_a_priori + self._predict_log_conditionals(x))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Punto 13\n",
    "\n",
    "13. Implementar el modelo `EfficientChol` combinando los insights de `EfficientQDA` y `TensorizedChol`. Si se desea, se puede implementar `FasterChol` como ayuda, pero no se contempla para el punto."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class EfficientChol(TensorizedChol):\n",
    "    \"\"\"QDA implementation that uses Cholesky decomposition for the covariance\n",
    "    matrices. Can predict multiple observations.\"\"\"\n",
    "    def __init__(self):\n",
    "        super(EfficientChol, self).__init__()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def predict(self, X):\n",
    "        \"\"\"For a (𝑝, 𝑛) array, return a (1, 𝑛) array with a prediction for each observation.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Check for appropriate shape in case of single prediction.\n",
    "        X = np.expand_dims(X, axis=1) if len(X.shape) == 1 else X\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # First, we need the unbiased X tensor.\n",
    "        ub_X = X - self.tensor_means                                          # Shape (𝑘, 𝑝, 𝑛)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Get quadratic form.\n",
    "        y = self.tensor_L_invs @ ub_X                                         # Shape (𝑘,𝑝,𝑝) * (𝑘,𝑝,𝑛) = (𝑘,𝑝,𝑛)\n",
    "        q_form = (y**2).sum(axis=1)                                           # Shape (𝑘,𝑝,𝑛) -sum-> (𝑘,𝑛)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Determinant calculation.\n",
    "        det_arr = np.log(\n",
    "            np.diagonal(\n",
    "                self.tensor_L_invs, offset=0, axis1=1, axis2=2\n",
    "            ).prod(axis=1)\n",
    "        )                                                                     # Shape (𝑘,𝑝,𝑝) -diag-> (𝑘,𝑝) -prod-> (𝑘,)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Now, we just need to calculate the log conditional.\n",
    "        log_conditional = np.expand_dims(det_arr, axis=1) - 0.5*q_form        # Shape (𝑘, 1) - shape (𝑘, 𝑛) = shape (𝑘, 𝑛)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Get the sum of the (logarithmic) prior and conditional\n",
    "        logsum = np.expand_dims(self.log_a_priori, axis=1) + log_conditional  # Shape (𝑘, 1) + shape (𝑘, 𝑛) = shape (𝑘, 𝑛)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Now we need the class that maximizes the logsum (for each observation)\n",
    "        return np.argmax(logsum, axis=0, keepdims=True)                       # Shape (1, 𝑛), as desired."
   ]
  },
